<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-10-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="638" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Lee</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-10-08"><hi rend="italic">October 8,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your dispatch
                            No. 160, of the 3d instant, with inclosure, relative to the fate of
                            Charles Govin, and in reply you are informed that your action in
                            demanding of the Governor and Captain General of Cuba the name of the
                            subordinate general who made the report of the death of Mr. Govin and
                            the name of the place at which it was written is approved by the
                            Department.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>